What is it?
Cohere is an enterprise-focused artificial intelligence platform that provides large language models (LLMs), generative AI capabilities, embeddings, retrieval, and AI agents. It is designed for organizations that want to deploy AI securely while maintaining control over their data.
What does it do?
Cohere provides:

Large Language Models (LLMs) for text generation and summarization
Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
AI-powered search and question answering
Document analysis and knowledge management
Text classification and sentiment analysis
AI agents that can perform multi-step tasks
Embeddings for semantic search and retrieval
Private deployment options (cloud, VPC, or on-premises)

Common use cases include:

Chatbots and virtual assistants
Enterprise search
Policy and procedure lookup
Customer support automation
Compliance and regulatory document analysis
Content generation and summarization

Who would use it?
Departments most likely to deploy Cohere:

Data Engineering — building internal semantic search and document retrieval pipelines across policy and claims data
IT and Infrastructure — managing private deployment, VPC configuration, and model hosting within USAA's security perimeter
Enterprise AI / Innovation Teams — evaluating and operationalizing LLM capabilities across business units
Member Services / Contact Center — powering AI-assisted search for agents handling member inquiries
Legal, Compliance, and Risk — surfacing regulatory documents, policy language, and audit trails through intelligent search
Security Risk — leveraging access controls, audit logging, and red-teaming outputs for model oversight
Claims and Underwriting — automating document summarization and structured data extraction from complex files

Roles most likely hands-on with the platform:

AI/ML Engineers and Data Scientists building and fine-tuning RAG pipelines
Enterprise Architects designing secure deployment topology
AI Governance and Risk leads (your lane) — evaluating vendor controls, classifying model risk, and mapping Cohere's compliance certifications to SR 11-7 and NIST AI RMF requirements
IT Security and IAM teams managing identity provider integrations and role-based access
Product Owners sponsoring AI-enabled workflows within business units

What business problem does it solve?
Cohere solves the problem of enterprise AI adoption under regulatory and data sovereignty pressure. Cohere helps organizations unlock value from large amounts of unstructured data (documents, emails, policies, knowledge bases, and records) by enabling employees and customers to find information, generate content, and automate knowledge-based tasks using AI.

